@SD_rocks:  I'm really not sure why you're so emotionally (and crudely) defending the choice to put a long-distance picture of a screen that happened to use an "HD" cam to capture it in this classification.  There is a separate classification for CAMs, and the two are distinct for a reason--it's not a technical distinction.  It's for ease of searching and honest classification of the end resullts.

Also, uploaders may wish to consider that blurring those lines harms their cred, if that matters.  I suppose an MPAA plant would actually love it, but for everyone else... :)
Also, leaked screeners have produced GREAT copies of movies, often BEFORE their theatrical release.  It's not "dmumb" at all.  I've seen it often, though less commonly now.

HD stands for High Definition, with respect to aspect ratio and resolution, there is no definite correlation to fidelity, which is what everyone here is bitching about.  1280x544 resolution is generally accepted as HD on torrent sites.  This uploader put TS in the title, which clearly indicates the quality of the movie.  Before bitching about how retarded the uploader is, learn more about the common conventions and some common courtesy.
